An American has become the sixth wingsuit flyer to die in the Alps in as many months, it emerged today.

The 33-year-old from California, who has not been named, plunged to earth near the French resort town of Chamonix on Saturday.

His horrific death follows that of former British soldier Mark Sutton, who performed the James Bond stunt at the opening ceremony at the London Olympics last year.

