Last year Chamonix banned wingsuit jumps after the death of a Norwegian jumper, who died when his parachute failed to open.

Mayor Eric Fournier said: ‘For us, adventure doesn't mean extreme risk. This is why the ban was brought in.’

It was lifted in July this year, however, following complaints from extreme sportsmen who argued that they were responsible for their own safety.

‘A new ban is a possibility,’ said a town council source. ‘The number of deaths associated with the sport is of great concern. Safety is always the priority.’

